1- BACKGROUND IMAGE

body {
    background-image: url('file-20180226-140213-yox11e.jpg');
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-attachment : fixed;    
    background-size: 100% 100%;
}

2- HOW TO BRING OBJECT TO THE CENTER OF SCREEN

div{
    width: 50%;
    height: 50%;
    position: fixed;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%,-50%);
}

3- WRITING TEXT AT THE BOTTOM OF A DIV ELEMENT

(first enclose it in a div component which has position property set relative)

.bottomright {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 8px;
  right: 16px;
  font-size: 18px;
}

4- ADDING FONT STYLE TO TEXT

font-family: "Lucida Console", Courier, monospace;
(We add 3 as if the browser failed to load one, then will go for next one.)


5- DIFFERENCE BETWEEN JUSTIFY CONTENT AND ALIGN ITEMS AND ALIGN CONTENT

    Justify-content will justify your flex items on main axix.
    align-items will align your flex items on cross axis.
    align-content will align multiple rows of your flex items in the cross axis.

